cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image restoration and generation using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). The paper proposes a novel approach to maintaining natural image statistics by explicitly looking at the distribution of features in an image and training the network to generate images with natural feature distributions. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of adversarial training (GAN) and the contextual loss, which are both techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions high-resolution surface normal estimation, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a common problem in multimedia (cs.MM).
